  <section class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 py-16 md:px-10 md:py-24 a-brand-a">
    <h2 class="text-center text-3xl font-extrabold text-navy lg:text-5xl">Frequently asked questions</h2>
    
    <dl class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-x-8 md:grid-cols-2 md:gap-x-12 mt-10">
      
        <div class="divide-y divide-gray-100 border-t border-gray-100">
          
            
              <div x-data="{ open: false }">
                <dt>
                  <button class="group flex w-full items-start justify-between gap-4 py-5 text-left" x-on:click="open = !open" :aria-expanded="open" aria-controls="faq-answer-1">
                    <span class="text-lg font-semibold leading-snug text-navy transition-colors group-hover:text-brand"> How long does it take to get started? </span>
                    <span class="mt-0.5 flex h-6 w-6 flex-shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-md border transition-all duration-200" :class="open ? 'bg-brand border-brand text-white rotate-45' : 'bg-brand/8 border-brand/25 text-brand'">
                      <i class="far fa-plus text-[10px]"></i>
                    </span>
                  </button>
                </dt>
                <dd id="faq-answer-1" x-show="open" x-transition:enter="transition ease-out duration-200" x-transition:enter-start="opacity-0 -translate-y-1" x-transition:enter-end="opacity-100 translate-y-0" x-transition:leave="transition ease-in duration-150" x-transition:leave-start="opacity-100 translate-y-0" x-transition:leave-end="opacity-0 -translate-y-1" class="-mt-1 pb-5 text-base leading-relaxed text-navy/60">
                  <p>Most teams configure their first mailbox and begin extracting data within minutes. There's no model training or dataset preparation required. You define your fields and start sending documents.</p>
                </dd>
              </div>
            
          
            
          
            
              <div x-data="{ open: false }">
                <dt>
                  <button class="group flex w-full items-start justify-between gap-4 py-5 text-left" x-on:click="open = !open" :aria-expanded="open" aria-controls="faq-answer-3">
                    <span class="text-lg font-semibold leading-snug text-navy transition-colors group-hover:text-brand"> What types of documents can Parseur handle? </span>
                    <span class="mt-0.5 flex h-6 w-6 flex-shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-md border transition-all duration-200" :class="open ? 'bg-brand border-brand text-white rotate-45' : 'bg-brand/8 border-brand/25 text-brand'">
                      <i class="far fa-plus text-[10px]"></i>
                    </span>
                  </button>
                </dt>
                <dd id="faq-answer-3" x-show="open" x-transition:enter="transition ease-out duration-200" x-transition:enter-start="opacity-0 -translate-y-1" x-transition:enter-end="opacity-100 translate-y-0" x-transition:leave="transition ease-in duration-150" x-transition:leave-start="opacity-100 translate-y-0" x-transition:leave-end="opacity-0 -translate-y-1" class="-mt-1 pb-5 text-base leading-relaxed text-navy/60">
                  <p>Parseur works with emails, PDFs, scanned documents, images, spreadsheets, and more formats across many industries and use cases.</p>
                </dd>
              </div>
            
          
            
          
            
              <div x-data="{ open: false }">
                <dt>
                  <button class="group flex w-full items-start justify-between gap-4 py-5 text-left" x-on:click="open = !open" :aria-expanded="open" aria-controls="faq-answer-5">
                    <span class="text-lg font-semibold leading-snug text-navy transition-colors group-hover:text-brand"> How does data retention work? </span>
                    <span class="mt-0.5 flex h-6 w-6 flex-shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-md border transition-all duration-200" :class="open ? 'bg-brand border-brand text-white rotate-45' : 'bg-brand/8 border-brand/25 text-brand'">
                      <i class="far fa-plus text-[10px]"></i>
                    </span>
                  </button>
                </dt>
                <dd id="faq-answer-5" x-show="open" x-transition:enter="transition ease-out duration-200" x-transition:enter-start="opacity-0 -translate-y-1" x-transition:enter-end="opacity-100 translate-y-0" x-transition:leave="transition ease-in duration-150" x-transition:leave-start="opacity-100 translate-y-0" x-transition:leave-end="opacity-0 -translate-y-1" class="-mt-1 pb-5 text-base leading-relaxed text-navy/60">
                  <p>You decide how long your data remains stored in Parseur. Retention settings are customizable per mailbox, so you stay in control of how your documents are handled.</p>
                </dd>
              </div>
            
          
            
          
            
              <div x-data="{ open: false }">
                <dt>
                  <button class="group flex w-full items-start justify-between gap-4 py-5 text-left" x-on:click="open = !open" :aria-expanded="open" aria-controls="faq-answer-7">
                    <span class="text-lg font-semibold leading-snug text-navy transition-colors group-hover:text-brand"> How does Parseur handle data privacy and regulations? </span>
                    <span class="mt-0.5 flex h-6 w-6 flex-shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-md border transition-all duration-200" :class="open ? 'bg-brand border-brand text-white rotate-45' : 'bg-brand/8 border-brand/25 text-brand'">
                      <i class="far fa-plus text-[10px]"></i>
                    </span>
                  </button>
                </dt>
                <dd id="faq-answer-7" x-show="open" x-transition:enter="transition ease-out duration-200" x-transition:enter-start="opacity-0 -translate-y-1" x-transition:enter-end="opacity-100 translate-y-0" x-transition:leave="transition ease-in duration-150" x-transition:leave-start="opacity-100 translate-y-0" x-transition:leave-end="opacity-0 -translate-y-1" class="-mt-1 pb-5 text-base leading-relaxed text-navy/60">
                  <p>Parseur is EU-hosted and aligned with major data protection regulations including EU GDPR, UK GDPR, California CCPA/CPRA, and Singapore PDPA. Data residency is maintained in the EU, and customers control their data retention settings.</p>
                </dd>
              </div>
            
          
            
          
            
              <div x-data="{ open: false }">
                <dt>
                  <button class="group flex w-full items-start justify-between gap-4 py-5 text-left" x-on:click="open = !open" :aria-expanded="open" aria-controls="faq-answer-9">
                    <span class="text-lg font-semibold leading-snug text-navy transition-colors group-hover:text-brand"> Can I upgrade, downgrade, or cancel at any time? </span>
                    <span class="mt-0.5 flex h-6 w-6 flex-shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-md border transition-all duration-200" :class="open ? 'bg-brand border-brand text-white rotate-45' : 'bg-brand/8 border-brand/25 text-brand'">
                      <i class="far fa-plus text-[10px]"></i>
                    </span>
                  </button>
                </dt>
                <dd id="faq-answer-9" x-show="open" x-transition:enter="transition ease-out duration-200" x-transition:enter-start="opacity-0 -translate-y-1" x-transition:enter-end="opacity-100 translate-y-0" x-transition:leave="transition ease-in duration-150" x-transition:leave-start="opacity-100 translate-y-0" x-transition:leave-end="opacity-0 -translate-y-1" class="-mt-1 pb-5 text-base leading-relaxed text-navy/60">
                  <p>Yes. All plan changes are self-service. You can upgrade, downgrade, or cancel directly from your account settings at any time, no sales calls or hoops required.</p>
                </dd>
              </div>
            
          
            
          
        </div>
      
        <div class="divide-y divide-gray-100 border-t border-gray-100">
          
            
          
            
              <div x-data="{ open: false }">
                <dt>
                  <button class="group flex w-full items-start justify-between gap-4 py-5 text-left" x-on:click="open = !open" :aria-expanded="open" aria-controls="faq-answer-2">
                    <span class="text-lg font-semibold leading-snug text-navy transition-colors group-hover:text-brand"> Do I need a developer to use Parseur? </span>
                    <span class="mt-0.5 flex h-6 w-6 flex-shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-md border transition-all duration-200" :class="open ? 'bg-brand border-brand text-white rotate-45' : 'bg-brand/8 border-brand/25 text-brand'">
                      <i class="far fa-plus text-[10px]"></i>
                    </span>
                  </button>
                </dt>
                <dd id="faq-answer-2" x-show="open" x-transition:enter="transition ease-out duration-200" x-transition:enter-start="opacity-0 -translate-y-1" x-transition:enter-end="opacity-100 translate-y-0" x-transition:leave="transition ease-in duration-150" x-transition:leave-start="opacity-100 translate-y-0" x-transition:leave-end="opacity-0 -translate-y-1" class="-mt-1 pb-5 text-base leading-relaxed text-navy/60">
                  <p>No. Non-technical teams can configure extraction and exports directly in the web app. If you need deeper integration, developers can use the API to automate everything programmatically.</p>
                </dd>
              </div>
            
          
            
          
            
              <div x-data="{ open: false }">
                <dt>
                  <button class="group flex w-full items-start justify-between gap-4 py-5 text-left" x-on:click="open = !open" :aria-expanded="open" aria-controls="faq-answer-4">
                    <span class="text-lg font-semibold leading-snug text-navy transition-colors group-hover:text-brand"> What happens when document formats change? </span>
                    <span class="mt-0.5 flex h-6 w-6 flex-shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-md border transition-all duration-200" :class="open ? 'bg-brand border-brand text-white rotate-45' : 'bg-brand/8 border-brand/25 text-brand'">
                      <i class="far fa-plus text-[10px]"></i>
                    </span>
                  </button>
                </dt>
                <dd id="faq-answer-4" x-show="open" x-transition:enter="transition ease-out duration-200" x-transition:enter-start="opacity-0 -translate-y-1" x-transition:enter-end="opacity-100 translate-y-0" x-transition:leave="transition ease-in duration-150" x-transition:leave-start="opacity-100 translate-y-0" x-transition:leave-end="opacity-0 -translate-y-1" class="-mt-1 pb-5 text-base leading-relaxed text-navy/60">
                  <p>Because extraction is instruction-based rather than trained on large sample datasets, Parseur adapts more easily to layout changes. You can also refine fields or rules at any time without retraining a model.</p>
                </dd>
              </div>
            
          
            
          
            
              <div x-data="{ open: false }">
                <dt>
                  <button class="group flex w-full items-start justify-between gap-4 py-5 text-left" x-on:click="open = !open" :aria-expanded="open" aria-controls="faq-answer-6">
                    <span class="text-lg font-semibold leading-snug text-navy transition-colors group-hover:text-brand"> Is Parseur secure? </span>
                    <span class="mt-0.5 flex h-6 w-6 flex-shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-md border transition-all duration-200" :class="open ? 'bg-brand border-brand text-white rotate-45' : 'bg-brand/8 border-brand/25 text-brand'">
                      <i class="far fa-plus text-[10px]"></i>
                    </span>
                  </button>
                </dt>
                <dd id="faq-answer-6" x-show="open" x-transition:enter="transition ease-out duration-200" x-transition:enter-start="opacity-0 -translate-y-1" x-transition:enter-end="opacity-100 translate-y-0" x-transition:leave="transition ease-in duration-150" x-transition:leave-start="opacity-100 translate-y-0" x-transition:leave-end="opacity-0 -translate-y-1" class="-mt-1 pb-5 text-base leading-relaxed text-navy/60">
                  <p>Parseur follows industry best security practices and undergoes regular third-party security testing. We are currently completing SOC 2 Type II and HIPAA compliance programs. Customer data is never reused to train our AI models and is never sold.</p>
                </dd>
              </div>
            
          
            
          
            
              <div x-data="{ open: false }">
                <dt>
                  <button class="group flex w-full items-start justify-between gap-4 py-5 text-left" x-on:click="open = !open" :aria-expanded="open" aria-controls="faq-answer-8">
                    <span class="text-lg font-semibold leading-snug text-navy transition-colors group-hover:text-brand"> Do I need a credit card to try Parseur? </span>
                    <span class="mt-0.5 flex h-6 w-6 flex-shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-md border transition-all duration-200" :class="open ? 'bg-brand border-brand text-white rotate-45' : 'bg-brand/8 border-brand/25 text-brand'">
                      <i class="far fa-plus text-[10px]"></i>
                    </span>
                  </button>
                </dt>
                <dd id="faq-answer-8" x-show="open" x-transition:enter="transition ease-out duration-200" x-transition:enter-start="opacity-0 -translate-y-1" x-transition:enter-end="opacity-100 translate-y-0" x-transition:leave="transition ease-in duration-150" x-transition:leave-start="opacity-100 translate-y-0" x-transition:leave-end="opacity-0 -translate-y-1" class="-mt-1 pb-5 text-base leading-relaxed text-navy/60">
                  <p>No. You can sign up and start extracting data for free without entering any payment information. Parseur includes a free tier so you can test it with your own documents before committing.</p>
                </dd>
              </div>
            
          
            
          
            
              <div x-data="{ open: false }">
                <dt>
                  <button class="group flex w-full items-start justify-between gap-4 py-5 text-left" x-on:click="open = !open" :aria-expanded="open" aria-controls="faq-answer-10">
                    <span class="text-lg font-semibold leading-snug text-navy transition-colors group-hover:text-brand"> Can Parseur handle high volumes or business-critical workflows? </span>
                    <span class="mt-0.5 flex h-6 w-6 flex-shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-md border transition-all duration-200" :class="open ? 'bg-brand border-brand text-white rotate-45' : 'bg-brand/8 border-brand/25 text-brand'">
                      <i class="far fa-plus text-[10px]"></i>
                    </span>
                  </button>
                </dt>
                <dd id="faq-answer-10" x-show="open" x-transition:enter="transition ease-out duration-200" x-transition:enter-start="opacity-0 -translate-y-1" x-transition:enter-end="opacity-100 translate-y-0" x-transition:leave="transition ease-in duration-150" x-transition:leave-start="opacity-100 translate-y-0" x-transition:leave-end="opacity-0 -translate-y-1" class="-mt-1 pb-5 text-base leading-relaxed text-navy/60">
                  <p>Yes. Parseur is built for production use, with uptime consistently above 99.9% and systems designed for reliability and redundancy. Many teams rely on it for real-time document flows where delays are not acceptable.</p>
                </dd>
              </div>
            
          
        </div>
      
    </dl>
